#Sterotype Annotations

1. @Component
2. @Service     -(business logic)
3. @Repository  -(data access logic)
4. @Controller  -(presentation logic)

#Component auto-scanning


@Repository(value="dao")
class AccountDao{
}

here above class will registered with "dao" id.


If our spring bean is in protype scope then, Spring
container will not manage the lifecycle of spring bean
after giving the object to the client. i.i destroy method
will not be called on Spring Bean ibj in prototype scope



